ogists keep both the distance required by science and the empathy required for the analysis of lived experiences? The plurality of moralities has not received an explicit and focused attention until recently, when accelerated globalization often resulted in the collision of different value systems. Observing, describing and assessing values cross-culturally, the authors propose various methodological approaches to the study of moralities, illustrated with rich ethnographic accounts, thus offering a valuable guide for students of anthropology, sociology and cultural studies and for professionals concerned with the empirical and cross-cultural study of values.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aGoodale, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeintz, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeintz, Monica, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHowell, Signe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLadwig, Patrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRasanayagam, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Joel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRydstrøm, Helle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSykes, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidlok, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZigon, Jarrett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184545938340uhttps://www.degruyter.com